    "comment": "Rationale: Researchers found an enrichment of Crk-L in mouse adult and developing neuromuscular synapses by performing immunostaining using an antibody against Crk-L. Staining was found in synapses identified using alpha-Bungarotoxin-594 to label AChRs. Imaging was performed using confocal microscopy.\n\n10/4/2017 Pim:\n- \"extrinsic component...\" selected because the paper shows recruitment of Crk-L to the plasma membrane via interaction with another protein.. Experimental description: Experiments were done in mouse myotubes/muscles.\nFrom M&M: \"For protein identification, the digests were analyzed\nby LC/ESI-MS/MS, using a nanoAquity UPLC coupled directly\nto a Q-TOF Premier MS (Waters). The proteins were identified\nusing MASCOT (MatrixScience) to search the NCBInr mouse-\nrat protein sequence database\"",
